<p>I am currently a lecturer in the <a href="http://www.maths.ed.ac.uk/">School of Mathematics</a> at the <a href="http://www.ed.ac.uk/">University of Edinburgh</a>, and a member of the <a href="http://www.maxwell.ac.uk/">Maxwell Institute for Mathematical Sciences</a>.</p>

<p>Previous to this, I have been a postdoc in the groups of <a href="http://www.imperial.ac.uk/AP/faces/pages/read/Home.jsp?person=s.kalliadasis&amp;_adf.ctrl-state=noxc94gbi_3&amp;_afrRedirect=292205271445195&quot;&gt;Serafim Kalliadasis">Serafim Kalliadasis</a> (<a href="http://www3.imperial.ac.uk/">Imperial College</a>, <a href="http://www3.imperial.ac.uk/complexmultiphasesystems">Chemical Engineering</a>) and <a href="http://www.mathematik.tu-darmstadt.de/~betz/">Volker Betz</a> (<a href="http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/">University of Warwick</a>, <a href="http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/fac/sci/maths/">Mathematics</a>, now <a href="http://www.tu-darmstadt.de/index.en.jsp">TU Darmstadt</a>, <a href="http://www3.mathematik.tu-darmstadt.de/en/fb/mathe/startseite.html">Mathematics</a>).  I undertook my PhD under <a href="http://www-m7.ma.tum.de/bin/view/Analysis/GeroFriesecke">Gero Friesecke</a> (University of Warwick, Maths, now <a href="http://www.tum.de/en/homepage/">TU Munich</a>, 
<a href="http://www-m7.ma.tum.de/bin/view/Analysis/WebHome">Mathematics</a>).</p>

<p>Broadly speaking, my research concerns modelling, analysis and numerics for complex, multiscale systems.  My work has applications in chemistry, physics, engineering and biology.  Both the areas and techniques used in my research are very wide-ranging. I’m always happy to discuss my work with anyone, especially mathematicians, applied scientists, and prospective PhD students.</p>

